/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.name: Affection
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.description: Dolphins are very affectionate with one another. There is a lot of stroking between mothers and calves; females and females; males and males as well as females and males.

videos.caption: Flipper Footsie is a phrase I have coined to describe their rubbing their pecs against each other.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.name: Bubbles
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.description: Some bubbles appear to be in play. Others appear to be a warning.

videos.caption: The female dolphin in this clip blows what could be interpreted as a warning bubble toward JoJo the male dolphin. Her lying on the bottom is very unusual behavior perhaps she was rejecting his advances.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.name: Fishing
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.description: Crater fishing is when a dolphin uses echolocation to find fish under the sand. They plunge their rostrum into the sand and bring up a fish.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.name: Behavior
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.description:
I’ve been swimming with JoJo for over twelve years. JoJo is a wild bottlenose dolphin that has made his home around the Turks and Caicos Islands. He is an ambassador dolphin which means he interacts with humans. My friendship with JoJo has grown over the years. I feel he trusts me enough to not only spend hours swimming with me but to bring me to meet many of his friends and perhaps family. He is very deliberate about coming over to our boat where I get in the water with him and he slowly brings me to meet mothers and calves.

Description: seven feet long, tip of his left flipper missing, left eye partially closed, slight nick on his dorsal and missing a small piece at the very end.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.name: Harassing Nurse Sharks
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.description: It appears bottlenose dolphins like to pester nurse sharks! I have seen it many times. They seem to take great sport in poking them with their rostrum or just closely following them. The nurse sharks instigated none of the dolphin behavior. On one occasion a dolphin really harassed a nurse shark by poking him with his rostrum. The nurse shark and dolphin were whirling in circles under me. The dolphin abruptly left and the nurse shark came after me. I returned to my boat and got out of the water. The nurse shark followed me right to the boat.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.name: Playing
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.description: Dolphins love to play. They are creative and opportunistic with their play!

sections.title: Dolphin Jewelry
sections.description: Dolphins like to drape seaweed over their pectoral fins (pecs), flukes and rostrums in play. I call it accessorizing!

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.name: Nursing
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.description: Calves nurse from their moms by pressing their rostrums into their mother’s mammillary slit. The mom squirts some rich milk into their mouth.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.name: Sex
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.description: It’s hard to distinguish the sex of dolphins unless they have a calf by their side or a male displays. Dolphins clearly enjoy sex and have no stigmas attached to any arrangement of partners.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.name: Signature Whistle
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/be.description: Dolphins greet each other with their own signature whistle, which is thought to be their name.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.name: Bo
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.description: Lemon Lip's Mom. She seems to be good friends with Raggedy Anne. I met Bo and Lemon Lips in 2012. No distinguishing marks except for a slight white spot on the front of her dorsal. Very friendly, seems to like it when Lemon Lips swims with me. Maybe gives her a rest! B.B.Tip and Raggedy Anne will swim close to me when all of them are together. Bo seems to want me in the pod.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.name: Julia & Frisky
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.description: Julia is a smaller mother she has an old scar on her left side below her dorsal. She is friendly with Raggedy Ann and of course JoJo. I think Frisky is in his second year. He just got a tear where is left pec attaches to his body. I don't know if that will create a scar. I have seen them numerous times this winter 2013-14 and been able to swim with them all but once.

videos.caption: JoJo is bringing me to Julia and Frisky. He is the biggest of the dolphins.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.name: Mojo
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.description: JoJo introduced me to him November 2009. I believe I had met him when he was a calf but I’m not sure. They have brought me for swims with Mo on my left and JoJo on my right. Mo will swim with me when JoJo isn’t around. He had a friend last year and they let me hang with them. He will go to boats and is okay with people swimming around.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.name: Lemon Lips
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.description: Bo’s calf. He was quite small in 2012. Has yellow lips. Maybe from Mom’s milk? Has lots of energy, whizzes all over. Circles me at speed then shoots off to visit others and comes back as if to tell me to hurry up! Has jumped over me, almost fallen into me. He's a real hot ticket! Seen him nurse and play with B.B.Tip. My most favorite calf.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.name: Raggedy Anne
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.description: JoJo introduced me to her and her calf Baby Black Tip in 2012. The left side of her fluke is ragged along the edge. Her calf was fairly large, maybe two years old. His dorsal is black on the very end. BB Tip is somewhat interested in me and on occasion will swim up to me. Raggedy Anne keeps her distance unless Bo and Lemon Lips are around. I have been able to observe BB Tip nursing. He is also learning to crater fish.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.name: Piney
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.description: I called him Bruiser for a while because he had so many nicks as if he’s been in a fight. They are located before his dorsal. When I met him in 2012 and he was very skinny. I’m not sure of his gender but he is usually by himself near the end of Pine Cay. He has let me swim with him on occasion when he’s by himself. One time I was with him while he was fishing. When there is a meeting of JoJo and the moms and calves he’s very friendly with me.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.name: Whitey
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.description: Whitey is a seven foot dolphin with white on her dorsal and on the right end of her fluke. The left side of her fluke has a small snip off the end and both sides are ragged. Both fins are also ragged. I met her Dec 26th 2013 she appeared to know me. She didn't want anything to do with tour boats and left immediately upon their arrival. This happened on both encounters that day. I don't actually know the sex and would guess maybe female because Whitey was visiting Julia and Frisky. She clearly came from outside the reef when we saw her the second time.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.name: Scarside
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.description: Met Scarside and her calf in the summer of 2012. They were swimming with JoJo and Raggedy Anne and B.B. Tip. She had a long gash behind her pec on the right side. Her calf swam right up to me and made his signature whistle. He had slightly yellow lips like Lemon Lips!

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.name: Snipper
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.description: Snipper showed up with JoJo and Whizzer in 2017. Whizzer is now three years old and has left Bo his Mom. Calves usually leave their mothers at this age. It is typical of young male dolphins to join other male dolphins when they leave their moms. I think JoJo has orchestrated this relationship because he's so friendly with both dolphins.I have included a picture of what I think is the same dolphin from 2011. He was with JoJo when I took this picture.

/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.name: Whizzer
/Users/maxbaun/Projects/JoJo/src/data/fr.description: Whizzer is Bo's calf born somewhere between July 2015 and October 2015. He would be Lemon Lips younger brother. He acts just like Lemon Lips and even has a yellow tinge to his lips. I think Bo produces very energetic calves and she seems to like my interacting with them. She has let me calf sit for both calves while she's off fishing or hanging with either JoJo or Raggedy Ann. This summer Raggedy Ann lost her calf and she has been helping Bo raise Whizzer.
